Kate Widdows is a graphic designer, letterer and neon GIF maker. She has designed typefaces for Nike, neon GIFs for the Huffington Post and Selena Gomez, and record covers for Sublime Frequencies and Drag City. She's hoping to finish a typeface called 'Oyster' sometime this century. An adept photographer and illustrator, Kate is also a visual artist in abstract watercolor, calligraphic experiments and neon, and plays the accordion. She's lived in New York, New England, Seattle and Geneva, and currently resides in Portland, Oregon.
